WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:14.630
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:17.540
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:20.370
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:23.480
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.110
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:41.040
Mirai dake shinjiteru dareka ga warattemo kamawanai
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:46.560
Hashitteru jounetsu ga anata wo KIRA mekaseru
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:52.100
Mabushi sugi, demo mitsumete itai
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:56.080
Dokka "bigaku" kanjiteru
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:56.080 --> 00:00:58.120
I'm really really stuck on you

12
00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:02.700
Dare ni mo nitenai yume no senaka wo
I follow, follow in the footsteps

13
00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.990
Oikakete oikaketeku
of a dream that resembles no one

14
00:01:05.990 --> 00:01:09.220
DORAMATIKKU te ni ireru made
Until I dramatically get it

15
00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:15.040
Believe in Wonderland!

16
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:21.120
Dare ni mo mienai yume no KATACHI wo
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

17
00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:24.200
Tsukamaete tsukamaeteku
of a dream no one can see

18
00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:30.220
Watashi wa tsuite yuku kara atsui KIMOCHI
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

19
00:01:30.460 --> 00:01:33.580
TSUJITSUMA awase betsu ni iranai
I don't really need everything to add up

20
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.750
Arifureta nichijou yori mo
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

21
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.350
PARADAISU mezashite hashire
run for paradise instead

22
00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:45.880
Believe in Wonderland!

23
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:54.340
Stowaway

24
00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:53.470
Yes...

25
00:01:53.470 --> 00:01:55.430
we managed to sink one ship...

26
00:01:55.430 --> 00:01:59.100
the one belonging to one
Bon Kurei, a Baroque Works agent.

27
00:01:59.100 --> 00:02:00.100
As for the other one...

28
00:02:00.480 --> 00:02:02.690
Hey, get a move on.

29
00:02:02.690 --> 00:02:04.560
So you let them get away...

30
00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:07.520
I can't believe I fell
for that cheap trick...

31
00:02:08.230 --> 00:02:10.740
They're good at running away.

32
00:02:13.240 --> 00:02:15.450
Miss Hina! Watch out!

33
00:02:15.450 --> 00:02:17.240
It really pisses me off.

34
00:02:17.240 --> 00:02:18.280
Hina's going crazy!

35
00:02:18.280 --> 00:02:20.040
Why? Because of
your incompetence?

36
00:02:23.500 --> 00:02:25.830
No, that's not it.

37
00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.300
Wowza! Miss Hina's Cage-Cage Fruit
always gives me the tingles!

38
00:02:32.300 --> 00:02:36.010
"Everything that touches
my body will be locked up."

39
00:02:36.390 --> 00:02:38.720
Say it! Say your killer line! You gotta!

40
00:02:42.310 --> 00:02:44.940
What the hell is this?!
An iron lock...?!

41
00:02:44.940 --> 00:02:47.770
You're what's driving
me crazy, Smoker.

42
00:02:48.230 --> 00:02:49.820
Haven't heard that one before...

43
00:02:51.070 --> 00:02:51.820
Because...

44
00:02:52.320 --> 00:02:54.400
you almost seem happy...

45
00:02:54.950 --> 00:02:57.160
that Straw Hat got away.

46
00:02:57.160 --> 00:02:57.780
Huh...?

47
00:02:59.200 --> 00:03:00.660
Me?

48
00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:01.950
Why would I be?

49
00:03:01.950 --> 00:03:02.950
Who knows?

50
00:03:04.330 --> 00:03:08.420
And she spoke to me
so formally, saying...

51
00:03:08.420 --> 00:03:12.710
"I have something important
to discuss, Dadd– No... Father."

52
00:03:12.710 --> 00:03:17.140
Even for a king like me,
few things are harder to give up...

53
00:03:18.640 --> 00:03:20.850
than the title of "daddy."

54
00:03:21.180 --> 00:03:23.520
What are you saying, Your Majesty?!

55
00:03:37.110 --> 00:03:39.870
I still can't believe you're really gone...

56
00:03:42.330 --> 00:03:43.870
I can't even shed a tear...

57
00:03:46.410 --> 00:03:49.040
I wonder why... Pell...

58
00:04:00.090 --> 00:04:01.470
Fire! Fire!

59
00:04:12.730 --> 00:04:14.320
What is it, Toto?

60
00:04:14.320 --> 00:04:16.780
You've been laughing
ever since the speech.

61
00:04:16.780 --> 00:04:18.360
Good grief...

62
00:04:18.360 --> 00:04:20.950
Did those sandstorms
scramble your brain, old man?

63
00:04:21.700 --> 00:04:24.290
It's a secret. I won't tell a soul.

64
00:04:24.660 --> 00:04:25.790
Huh?

65
00:04:25.790 --> 00:04:27.540
What do you mean?

66
00:04:30.040 --> 00:04:32.590
Take care, Luffy!

67
00:04:32.590 --> 00:04:35.510
Come back sometime
and drink Yuba's water.

68
00:04:36.300 --> 00:04:37.380
– Huh?
– Huh?

69
00:04:40.430 --> 00:04:43.220
Now, why are you guys
just standing around?!

70
00:04:43.220 --> 00:04:44.970
That well won't dig itself!

71
00:04:44.970 --> 00:04:46.970
Yeah, yeah...

72
00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:55.980
♪ So if the world ever changes ♪
♪ I'll call out your name ♪

73
00:04:51.230 --> 00:04:55.230
Hey... Who do you think
the princess was talking to, anyway?

74
00:04:55.230 --> 00:04:57.610
Who knows and who cares?!

75
00:04:55.980 --> 00:05:03.070
♪ We could return to a time ♪
♪ when our lives were still the same ♪

76
00:04:57.610 --> 00:04:59.610
Princess Vivi's speech was so uplifting.

77
00:05:00.070 --> 00:05:02.240
We have to do our part!

78
00:05:02.240 --> 00:05:04.120
Yeah, that's right.

79
00:05:03.070 --> 00:05:10.370
♪ Take me to the place ♪
♪ where memories remain ♪

80
00:05:04.120 --> 00:05:05.950
Even though we're just commoners.

81
00:05:05.950 --> 00:05:07.750
We don't wanna hear it from you!

82
00:05:10.370 --> 00:05:17.460
♪ Please don't ever let them fade ♪

83
00:05:19.260 --> 00:05:22.510
As expected, Alubarna
seems to be in bad shape.

84
00:05:22.510 --> 00:05:25.100
Then let us make haste.

85
00:05:25.100 --> 00:05:27.310
Yuba's restoration is also a priority,

86
00:05:27.310 --> 00:05:29.730
since it's a crucial
crossroad in the west.

87
00:05:29.730 --> 00:05:32.940
Don't forget about fixing
the Sandora River canals.

88
00:05:32.940 --> 00:05:34.560
But what about the casino?

89
00:05:34.560 --> 00:05:36.480
It's closing down.

90
00:05:36.480 --> 00:05:37.780
Let's go, everyone!

91
00:05:37.780 --> 00:05:39.150
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

92
00:05:39.610 --> 00:05:42.660
So why're we giving
this guy special treatment?

93
00:05:42.660 --> 00:05:43.660
No clue...

94
00:05:43.660 --> 00:05:46.490
But it was an order from Princess Vivi.

95
00:05:46.490 --> 00:05:49.330
It even wants to join
the Supersonic Duck Squad.

96
00:05:51.910 --> 00:05:53.170
But it's a camel...

97
00:05:54.290 --> 00:05:55.670
Wow, you don't say?

98
00:05:58.880 --> 00:05:59.840
Well then...

99
00:05:59.840 --> 00:06:02.010
Thank you... for everything.

100
00:06:02.010 --> 00:06:04.470
Seriously, you're so impatient.

101
00:06:04.470 --> 00:06:06.970
I shouldn't let you go
anywhere in that state.

102
00:06:06.970 --> 00:06:08.220
I know. Farewell.

103
00:06:08.220 --> 00:06:12.230
Make sure to take it easy
once you're home! Got it?

104
00:06:12.230 --> 00:06:14.230
Yeah, I've got it.

105
00:06:14.600 --> 00:06:16.230
Oh... Hey, wait.

106
00:06:17.190 --> 00:06:19.150
You forgot this. Here.

107
00:06:40.880 --> 00:06:42.420
Now, Karoo!

108
00:06:46.590 --> 00:06:48.680
Let's go home... to Alubarna!

109
00:07:01.980 --> 00:07:03.740
Captain Smoker...

110
00:07:03.740 --> 00:07:05.280
Hey there, little lady.

111
00:07:05.280 --> 00:07:06.950
How's the leg treating you?

112
00:07:06.950 --> 00:07:10.330
P-Please stop talking like that.

113
00:07:21.170 --> 00:07:22.300
Thank you, though...

114
00:07:24.170 --> 00:07:27.220
I saw their new bounties...

115
00:07:27.220 --> 00:07:30.100
For them, these numbers
are no surprise.

116
00:07:30.100 --> 00:07:32.520
Do you know what
his swordsman buddy did?

117
00:07:32.520 --> 00:07:34.100
You mean Roronoa?

118
00:07:35.230 --> 00:07:38.350
He slew 100 bounty
hunters at Whisky Peak.

119
00:07:38.350 --> 00:07:42.480
In addition, he cut down
Daz Bonez in Alubarna.

120
00:07:42.480 --> 00:07:45.030
Daz? The infamous assassin?!

121
00:07:45.650 --> 00:07:49.200
He made a name for himself as
a bounty hunter in the West Blue,

122
00:07:49.200 --> 00:07:51.870
but in Baroque Works,
he was known as Mr. 1.

123
00:07:52.450 --> 00:07:59.290
Y'know, it's almost impressive how many
big shots Crocodile brought to heel.

124
00:07:59.630 --> 00:08:02.590
But even with all of them, he still lost.

125
00:08:02.920 --> 00:08:06.470
One of these days, we'll settle
things with the Straw Hats.

126
00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:08.050
Yes, sir!

127
00:08:09.430 --> 00:08:11.430
Looks like we ditched the Marines.

128
00:08:14.520 --> 00:08:17.100
Hey, isn't that good news?

129
00:08:21.360 --> 00:08:22.060
Seriously...

130
00:08:22.570 --> 00:08:25.280
what's with you sad sacks?!

131
00:08:26.320 --> 00:08:28.280
– I miss her!
– I miss her!

132
00:08:28.280 --> 00:08:29.950
Quit whining!

133
00:08:29.950 --> 00:08:32.950
If you wanted her
to stay with us that badly...

134
00:08:32.950 --> 00:08:34.540
you should've kidnapped her!

135
00:08:35.410 --> 00:08:36.290
You savage!

136
00:08:36.290 --> 00:08:37.410
You're the worst!

137
00:08:37.410 --> 00:08:38.410
Moss Head.

138
00:08:38.410 --> 00:08:39.620
Three-sword style...

139
00:08:39.620 --> 00:08:40.670
Hey, wait, Luffy.

140
00:08:40.670 --> 00:08:43.040
"Three-sword style" isn't an insult.

141
00:08:43.040 --> 00:08:44.000
Four-sword style.

142
00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:45.670
The number isn't the issue...

143
00:08:45.670 --> 00:08:47.720
Listen, it's like calling natto smelly.

144
00:08:47.720 --> 00:08:50.220
Of course fermented
soybeans are gonna stink...

145
00:08:50.590 --> 00:08:52.300
Finally, we're out to sea.

146
00:08:52.300 --> 00:08:52.970
Yeah.

147
00:08:54.510 --> 00:08:55.510
Nice job.

148
00:08:57.810 --> 00:08:59.480
You here for revenge?! Bring it!

149
00:08:59.850 --> 00:09:01.350
What is she doing here?

150
00:09:01.350 --> 00:09:04.770
Enemy attack! Enemy attack!

151
00:09:06.150 --> 00:09:07.070
Who is she?

152
00:09:07.070 --> 00:09:08.820
Who the hell cares?!

153
00:09:08.820 --> 00:09:10.400
What an absolute knockout!

154
00:09:17.580 --> 00:09:22.540
I thought I told you not
to point dangerous objects at me.

155
00:09:22.540 --> 00:09:24.500
How long have you been on board?!

156
00:09:24.500 --> 00:09:25.750
Oh, a while now.

157
00:09:26.250 --> 00:09:28.760
These are your clothes, right?
I'm borrowing them.

158
00:09:28.760 --> 00:09:31.720
What's your game, Baroque Works?!

159
00:09:31.720 --> 00:09:33.340
Monkey D. Luffy...

160
00:09:33.340 --> 00:09:37.470
You haven't forgotten
what you did to me, have you?

161
00:09:37.470 --> 00:09:42.060
Luffy! What'd you do to that
beautiful lady, you bastard?!

162
00:09:41.810 --> 00:09:45.020
Get off the ship immediately.

163
00:09:42.060 --> 00:09:45.020
Spit it out, you son of a bitch!

164
00:09:45.650 --> 00:09:49.110
Hey, quit lying! I didn't
do anything to you!

165
00:09:49.490 --> 00:09:50.360
Oh, but you did.

166
00:09:50.360 --> 00:09:52.990
And it was absolutely unbearable.

167
00:09:52.990 --> 00:09:55.240
So you need to take responsibility.

168
00:09:55.240 --> 00:09:58.410
Who's that and what's going on?

169
00:09:55.620 --> 00:09:59.080
What's this "unbearable"
thing you did, Luffy?!

170
00:09:56.740 --> 00:09:58.410
Leave the ship...

171
00:09:58.410 --> 00:10:00.830
or we will contact the Marines.

172
00:09:59.080 --> 00:10:03.460
You'd better take responsibility or...!

173
00:10:00.830 --> 00:10:03.460
I'm serious.

174
00:10:04.170 --> 00:10:07.290
Quit confusing me!
What the heck do you want?!

175
00:10:09.300 --> 00:10:11.760
I want... to join your crew.

176
00:10:11.760 --> 00:10:12.880
– Huh?!
– Huh?!

177
00:10:17.180 --> 00:10:19.060
Administer that right away.

178
00:10:19.060 --> 00:10:22.020
It's the antidote for Crocodile's venom.

179
00:10:22.350 --> 00:10:24.230
Even if he's buried in this rubble...

180
00:10:24.230 --> 00:10:26.730
he's made of rubber,
so he might survive.

181
00:10:29.070 --> 00:10:30.650
Before, you told Crocodile...

182
00:10:31.280 --> 00:10:34.570
that the only thing
recorded here is history...

183
00:10:37.620 --> 00:10:39.200
Why did you lie?

184
00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:43.000
So you knew...?

185
00:10:43.790 --> 00:10:44.830
How cruel...

186
00:10:45.370 --> 00:10:49.040
That stone tells nothing
of this country's history.

187
00:10:49.040 --> 00:10:53.090
It should only contain information
regarding the weapon you seek.

188
00:10:53.090 --> 00:10:54.970
And that includes its location.

189
00:10:55.340 --> 00:10:57.430
If you had told Crocodile,

190
00:10:57.430 --> 00:11:00.850
this country would've
fallen into his hands.

191
00:11:00.850 --> 00:11:02.180
Isn't that right?

192
00:11:03.560 --> 00:11:05.190
It's of no concern to me...

193
00:11:05.190 --> 00:11:10.150
Countries... People's lives...
I honestly couldn't care less.

194
00:11:10.520 --> 00:11:14.610
I never had any intention of
handing that weapon to Crocodile.

195
00:11:14.990 --> 00:11:16.950
I don't understand...

196
00:11:16.950 --> 00:11:18.620
Then why did you come here?

197
00:11:19.580 --> 00:11:21.950
I expected one thing,
but hoped for another.

198
00:11:23.250 --> 00:11:26.580
What I was hoping to find...
was the Rio Poneglyph.

199
00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:31.840
Of all the poneglyphs
scattered throughout the world,

200
00:11:31.840 --> 00:11:34.090
it alone tells the true history.

201
00:11:35.670 --> 00:11:37.510
That is the Rio Poneglyph.

202
00:11:39.050 --> 00:11:42.310
What do you mean "true history"?

203
00:11:43.810 --> 00:11:45.140
I don't care anymore...

204
00:11:45.140 --> 00:11:49.650
I've searched for twenty years,
exhausting every lead...

205
00:11:49.650 --> 00:11:53.530
This was my last hope...
but it was just another dead end.

206
00:11:53.530 --> 00:11:56.400
This is as fitting an end
as any for someone like me...

207
00:11:58.070 --> 00:12:01.700
I'm so tired... I don't think
I can live like this any longer.

208
00:12:06.580 --> 00:12:09.330
All I wanted was to know the history...

209
00:12:11.340 --> 00:12:12.840
But too many enemies...

210
00:12:13.460 --> 00:12:15.300
stand in the way of my dream.

211
00:12:16.170 --> 00:12:17.590
Let me ask you a question...

212
00:12:18.510 --> 00:12:22.010
Can the untold history
be brought to light?

213
00:12:22.010 --> 00:12:24.890
Are you saying that
the poneglyphs hold that record?

214
00:12:26.600 --> 00:12:29.020
Then why do we...

215
00:12:34.400 --> 00:12:35.650
Alright, let's go.

216
00:12:35.650 --> 00:12:36.610
Hold on!

217
00:12:36.610 --> 00:12:38.570
I no longer have any reason to live!

218
00:12:38.950 --> 00:12:40.240
Just leave me here!

219
00:12:41.620 --> 00:12:44.200
Why the heck should I listen to you?

220
00:12:48.410 --> 00:12:52.170
You made me live
when I wanted to die.

221
00:12:52.170 --> 00:12:54.000
That's your crime.

222
00:12:54.500 --> 00:12:57.760
I have nowhere to go
and no home to return to.

223
00:12:57.760 --> 00:13:00.260
So let me stay on this ship.

224
00:13:00.260 --> 00:13:03.510
Oh, I see... Then I guess we have
no choice. Welcome aboard.

225
00:13:03.510 --> 00:13:05.760
– Luffy!
– Luffy!

226
00:13:05.760 --> 00:13:07.770
Don't worry.

227
00:13:07.770 --> 00:13:09.730
She's not a bad person.

228
00:13:09.730 --> 00:13:11.850
Mellorine! Mellor–

229
00:13:32.040 --> 00:13:33.080
Pay attention!

230
00:13:33.460 --> 00:13:36.090
Answer my questions honestly!

231
00:13:36.090 --> 00:13:37.590
I'll ask you one more time.

232
00:13:37.590 --> 00:13:38.630
What's your name?!

233
00:13:39.920 --> 00:13:42.800
Oh... I'm Usopp, by the way.
Nice to meet you. Yep, nice to meet you.

234
00:13:42.800 --> 00:13:44.350
My name is Nico Robin.

235
00:13:44.350 --> 00:13:45.680
Okay, then, Nico Robin.

236
00:13:45.680 --> 00:13:47.310
What is your occupation?

237
00:13:47.310 --> 00:13:48.350
I'm an archaeologist.

238
00:13:48.350 --> 00:13:49.480
An archaeologist?!

239
00:13:49.850 --> 00:13:54.020
I actually come from a long
line of archaeologists.

240
00:13:54.020 --> 00:14:00.610
The whole "wanted criminal" thing didn't
happen until I was, oh... eight or so.

241
00:14:00.940 --> 00:14:02.780
That was twenty years ago.

242
00:14:02.780 --> 00:14:06.120
Ever since, I've had
to keep a low profile.

243
00:14:06.120 --> 00:14:09.450
Since you were eight?
You were alone that long?

244
00:14:11.460 --> 00:14:16.170
Well, no child could survive
on the sea completely alone.

245
00:14:16.960 --> 00:14:19.340
For my own protection,

246
00:14:19.340 --> 00:14:22.050
and to bring me closer to my goal,

247
00:14:22.720 --> 00:14:27.050
I've had to ally myself with
various scoundrels and outlaws.

248
00:14:27.050 --> 00:14:28.260
That's the gist, anyway.

249
00:14:29.260 --> 00:14:32.520
As such, I've become quite adept
at operating in the shadows.

250
00:14:32.520 --> 00:14:34.730
So I'm sure I can be
of use to you all as well.

251
00:14:34.730 --> 00:14:38.110
Oh...? You sure are confident...

252
00:14:38.110 --> 00:14:39.320
What's your specialty?

253
00:14:41.150 --> 00:14:42.150
Assassination.

254
00:14:42.150 --> 00:14:46.910
Luffy! My investigation has concluded
that she's way too dangerous!

255
00:14:47.910 --> 00:14:49.240
Are you guys listening?!

256
00:14:49.990 --> 00:14:51.660
Seriously...!

257
00:14:52.040 --> 00:14:54.540
Being hoodwinked
so easily... Pathetic!

258
00:14:54.540 --> 00:14:57.880
A few days ago, she was
the VP of a crime syndicate.

259
00:14:58.380 --> 00:15:01.920
As if we'd let someone like her join us!

260
00:15:02.420 --> 00:15:06.430
You may have conned these
morons, but I'm not so easy!

261
00:15:06.430 --> 00:15:09.510
Make one wrong move
and you're out of here!

262
00:15:11.010 --> 00:15:13.730
Okay. I'll keep that in mind.

263
00:15:13.730 --> 00:15:15.600
Oh yeah, almost forgot...

264
00:15:15.600 --> 00:15:18.810
I brought some of
Crocodile's jewelry with me...

265
00:15:20.610 --> 00:15:23.320
Wow, Big Sis! I love you!

266
00:15:23.320 --> 00:15:24.530
– Hey, hey, hey, hey...
– Hey, hey, hey, hey...

267
00:15:24.530 --> 00:15:26.280
Nami's been suckered.

268
00:15:26.280 --> 00:15:27.780
That was a dirty trick.

269
00:15:27.780 --> 00:15:29.530
She's totally under her spell.

270
00:15:29.530 --> 00:15:30.660
– Huh?
– Huh?

271
00:15:32.830 --> 00:15:34.710
Oh, love...

272
00:15:34.710 --> 00:15:36.000
Floating love...

273
00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:40.710
I'm driftwood that just lays
its burnt body in that stream...

274
00:15:41.710 --> 00:15:42.710
Treasure...

275
00:15:42.710 --> 00:15:44.670
I'm driftwood that has been struck by

276
00:15:44.670 --> 00:15:47.800
your thunderbolt of beauty
and is caught in a raging torrent...

277
00:15:48.680 --> 00:15:49.930
A snack for you, my lady.

278
00:15:49.930 --> 00:15:51.390
Oh, thank you.

279
00:15:51.390 --> 00:15:53.600
Welp, saw that one coming.

280
00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:54.430
Yeah...

281
00:15:54.430 --> 00:15:57.100
He never stood a chance, anyway...

282
00:15:57.100 --> 00:15:58.230
In any case...

283
00:15:59.190 --> 00:16:02.940
now that it's come to this,
it's up to us to hold the line.

284
00:16:02.940 --> 00:16:06.360
Yeah, they're so naive!
Buncha pushovers...

285
00:16:06.360 --> 00:16:07.820
Hey, Usopp!

286
00:16:06.900 --> 00:16:07.820
What?!

287
00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:09.870
Chopper!

288
00:16:16.540 --> 00:16:18.120
Should I call you "Robin my love"?

289
00:16:18.620 --> 00:16:20.250
Or should it be "Robin my sweet"...?

290
00:16:20.250 --> 00:16:21.960
Which should it be?

291
00:16:21.960 --> 00:16:23.170
Oh? Where're you going?

292
00:16:27.340 --> 00:16:29.380
What a woman...

293
00:16:29.380 --> 00:16:33.310
Unlike Nami, she's got
a certain mature allure about her...

294
00:16:38.190 --> 00:16:40.440
This ship is nice...

295
00:16:40.440 --> 00:16:42.440
Is it always this lively?

296
00:16:43.190 --> 00:16:44.900
Yeah... It is.

297
00:16:45.480 --> 00:16:46.690
I see.

298
00:16:49.240 --> 00:16:52.070
What the hell is her angle?

299
00:16:58.330 --> 00:17:01.420
By the way, Miss Navigator...
Is it smooth sailing right now?

300
00:17:01.420 --> 00:17:03.920
Wind, weather... Both no problem!

301
00:17:03.920 --> 00:17:06.420
It's going very smoothly, Big Sis!

302
00:17:06.420 --> 00:17:08.800
So she paid you off, huh?

303
00:17:08.800 --> 00:17:10.930
Sanji, is my snack ready yet?!

304
00:17:10.930 --> 00:17:12.430
Hold your horses!
